      • processTest

        public static java.awt.image.BufferedImage processTest(java.awt.image.BufferedImage left,
                                                       java.awt.image.BufferedImage right,
                                                       ImageProcParams params)
        Processes two images, front left and front right. It stitches these and returns a windscreen image based on the given parameters.
        Parameters:
        left - windscreen left image
        right - windscreen right image
        params - the parameters used to process the image
        Returns:
        the windscreen image

      • process

        public abstract ImageOutputSet process(ImageInputSet input,
                                       boolean isJunction)
        Processes the set of five images in the input set. This method blocks and returns the result. Treat as a possibly lengthy method. The returned images are guarenteed to not be in place of the input images, so it is safe to deallocate the input images after this method call.
        Parameters:
        input - The input set of five images
        isJunction - if the front image contains a junction (means no headlights will be shown)
        Returns:
        The resulting four images
